rComments: Although the course was on social motivation, there was no need to make the term an experiment on individual educational motivation. The course material is actually very interesting subject matter, but the highly scattered nature of the lectures in conjunction with cryptic and subjective answer-seeking tests was not a positive experience.

I know her review isn't that great, but it's still possible to do well. She's kind and very approachable. It's true that the 7-10pm is long for this class. But if you just find the strength to attend class (you have to go to get your questionnaire completion points), you'll do fine!

I love taking 7-10s but this one was unbearable. It's almost impossible to tell whether she is just rambling or if what she's saying is important. Her questions were insanely specific. The good is that the concepts are interesting,  you learn to be a better version of yourself and how to attain future goals.
